    <h2 {...{
      "id": "perfectsquareterm1-operation-term2"
    }}><inlineCode parentName="h2">{`perfectSquare(term1, operation, term2)`}</inlineCode></h2>
    <p>{`In order to implement the perfect square formula in our code with Mathium, we must call the function using Mathium's API, as such:`}</p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-ts"
      }}>{`import * as Mathium from "mathiumjs";

let formula = Mathium.perfectSquare(term1, operation, term2);
`}</code></pre>
    <p>{`NOTE: The name `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`Mathium`}</inlineCode>{` after `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`* as`}</inlineCode>{` is arbitrary; it can be replaced with whatever you'd like:`}</p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-ts"
      }}>{`import * as foo from "mathiumjs";

let formula = foo.perfectSquare(term1, operation, term2);
`}</code></pre>
    <h2 {...{
      "id": "concept"
    }}>{`Concept`}</h2>
    <p>{`When any polynomial is multiplied by itself, then it is a perfect square.`}</p>
    <p>{`To expand any polynomial, we can apply one of the following patterns:`}</p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{}}>{`(a + b)^2 = a^2 + 2ab + b^2

(a - b)^2 = a^2 - 2ab - b^2
`}</code></pre>
    <p>{`NOTE: In these patterns, `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`a`}</inlineCode>{` and/or `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`b`}</inlineCode>{` can be replaced by any type of algebraic expression.`}</p>
    <p>{`For example, if we want to expand `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`(8x + 7x)^2`}</inlineCode>{`, `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`a = 8x`}</inlineCode>{` and `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`b = 7x`}</inlineCode>{`. Therefore...`}</p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{}}>{`(8x + 7x)^2 = (8x)^2 + 2(8x)(7x) + (7x)^2
`}</code></pre>
    <p>{`In our Mathium code, it's important to note the following:`}</p>
